during her tenure mrs thatcher championed free market 
policies believing fervently in deregulation free enterprise and 
competition 
she sold 64 billion worth of stateowned companies and more 
than tripled the number of shareholders to 11 million or 24 
percent of the population 
mrs thatcher also slashed and simplified taxes britains top 
tax bracket got the biggest reduction from 83 percent to 40 
percent while the basic rate dropped from 33 percent to 25 
percent 
wanting to encourage home ownership she sold more than 15 
million governmentowned dwellings to their tenants 
but many new homeowners are struggling to pay adjustable rate 
mortgages they climbed along with britains base lending rate 
which stood at 15 percent for a year until it came down to 14 
percent in october 
mrs thatcher curbed britains militant trade unions with 
legislation that required unions to hold referendums before going 
on strike the number of days lost to strikes shrank to 41 million 
last year from 295 million in 1979 union membership has fallen to 
84 million from 12 million 
mrs thatcher also tried to wean britons off the welfare state 
but spending on social security programs has gone up 41 percent in 
real terms in the past decade 
she put a tight grip on public spending turning budget deficits 
into budget surpluses but britains infrastructure suffered and 
the number of homeless has increased critics say 
she oversaw the deregulation of the financial markets under the 
socalled big bang which allowed more players into the market 
abolished minimum commissions allowed banks to enter the 
securities business and permitted foreign firms to join the stock 
exchange 
but the stock market boom evaporated in the october 1987 stock 
market crash low trading volume has hurt profits and forced job 
cutbacks at many investment firms 
the critics also say big bang which brought higher salaries 
bonuses and stock options created a yuppie class reviled by 
many for its market speculation and flashy lifestyles while mrs 
thatcher sought to promote selfreliance and industriousness she 
instead fostered greed and selfishness they say 
britain enjoyed a fiveyear real estate boom but now lots of 
office space goes begging for tenants particularly in the 
docklands the huge east london development that was to exemplify 
the best of thatcherism 
among her other achievements mrs thatcher took inflation from 
18 percent down to 3 percent in 1986 but it has climbed back up to 
109 percent higher than the 103 percent rate that she inherited 
in 1979 
she got 17 percent interest rates as low as 75 percent but 
they too have bounced back up 
the current number of unemployed is 17 million people and 
climbing higher than 11 million in 1979 the figure went as high 
as 3 million during mrs thatchers tenure 
