this restored colonial capital has long 
been a magnet for tourists lured by a city that once echoed with 
the speeches of the nations founding fathers lately however the 
visitor count has dropped 
tourism is down 10 percent for the year prompting the 
foundation that operates the 173acre attraction to offer hundreds 
