williamsburg became capital of englands virginia colony in 1699 
when nearby jamestown burned to the ground it was the colonial 
capital until 1776 and capital of virginia until 1779 
the city southeast of richmond was the scene of the convention 
of 1776 that instructed george washington and other virginia 
delegates to the continental congress the nations second oldest 
college william and mary was founded here in 1693 
nowadays guides wearing threecornered hats swords kneepants 
