<TEXT>
when mary hoffman joined the army during world 
war ii she was a serious young woman who thought shed already 
missed her chance for a full life but the womens auxiliary army 
corps changed everything 
i thought i was going to be a spinster she recalled 47 
years later instead i married my first bedside patient 
mrs hoffman is one of the 350000 women who served in world war 
ii she is also the largest single donor to the foundation thats 
trying to build a memorial to americas women veterans mrs 
