the army said those guerrillas belonged to the popular front for 
the liberation of palestine a plo faction led by george habash 
israel carved out the 440 square mile security zone as a buffer 
protecting its northern border against guerrilla raids in 1985 
when it withdrew the bulk of its forces from lebanon after a 
threeyear occupation 
the zone is jointly patrolled by israeli soldiers and some 2700 
members of the mostly christian south lebanon army 
