this is a golden time for speaker thomas s 
foley he has led his democrats from upheaval to unity has 
president bush courting on every issue and his side will enjoy a 
big 100vote majority beginning next month 
but what is his mandate 
the washington democrat became speaker last year after former 
speaker jim wright resigned in an ethics storm foleys soothing 
lowkey style was good medicine for the institution and built him a 
huge reservoir of good will 
given the mess he inherited he wasnt blamed for the slow pace 
of legislation last year or the sloppy way things were done this 
year and he won praise for what was accomplished in the end 
the 102nd congress however will be all his starting with his 
uncontested renomination by the democrats on monday 
speaker foley came during a difficult time and i think hes 
established a high level of confidence and trust i think he has 
strong bipartisan support and is an excellent speaker said rep 
dave mccurdy dokla 
i think the issue is how does he consolidate the gains he 
made mccurdy added 
in the last congress foley proved a patient negotiator with an 
extraordinary talent for nurturing consensus on issues ranging 
from flag burning where he outlasted demands for a constitutional 
amendment to the budget where he and the democrats stonewalled as 
bushs tax pledge crumbled he smartly waited for the consensus to 
move in his direction and won 
he seems to be utilizing those same skills as he fences with the 
white house over bushs middle east policy 
a protege of the late sen henry scoop jackson foley 
clearly understands that even if lawmakers doubt bush they cant 
let republicans trap them into appearing weak on defense issues 
his handling of the issue on behalf of the democrats could help set 
the tone for the new congress 
but the next congress will test not only whether foley can lead 
the democrats through the political mine fields hell be expected 
to put new ideas for the nations needs before his colleagues and 
the nation 
mccurdy and others say foley needs to develop legislative 
initiatives for the house that also will serve the party well in 
the 1992 presidential election 
so far foley has enunciated an agenda that only repeats his 
desire for some of the unfinished items from the last congress 
including campaign reform and civil rights legislation democratic 
leaders also intend to keep pushing the economic fairness issue 
they believe served the party well in the closing weeks of the last 
congress 
rep pat williams dmont a member of the democratic 
leadership expressed confidence foley will step out in front the 
speaker toughened politically he said when foleys initial budget 
deal with bush was defeated 
i think foley became a better poker player with the help of 
his democratic colleagues when they rejected the budget agreement 
they were dealt and asked for a new hand he said 
foleys position will be stronger also because of changes he can 
now make in the house leadership structure which he couldnt make 
midstream murky to the outside world they are nonetheless 
important 
new lawmakers will be beholden to him for their committee 
assignments the new democratic campaign chief is his pick and he 
gets to replace wright holdovers and appoint a big portion of the 
partys policymaking committee in the house 
foleys toughest challenge may be to temper his natural tendency 
to let issues come to him since theres no way to make sure the 
most vocal messagecarriers represent the partys best interests 
the leftwing screamers and the oneissue democrats need to 
let foley steer a mainstream course and to let foley be foley 
said mccurdy who promised he and other moderates would make sure 
they were in foleys face as often as the others were 
no one expects foley to change stripes to be anything but his 
cautious compromising intellectual self the real question is 
whether he will be expansive whether he will go beyond sorting 
through competing suggestions for curing the nations ills and 
develop them and push them to fruition 
with world and domestic events moving so quickly hell start 
providing answers soon after the new congress begins on jan 3 
 
editors note steven komarow covers congress for the 
associated press 
