townships to enforce the curfews which affected about 650000 
people 
about 1000 blacks have been killed in factional fighting in 
johannesburg townships since august thousands more have died in 
natal province where the battles have raged since 1985 
the fighting involves supporters of the inkatha freedom party 
who are mostly zulus and xhosas and other blacks who back the anc 
both groups oppose apartheid but differ on tactics for fighting it 
inkatha favors a more conservative approach than the anc 
several homes in tokoza were attacked and burned during the 
factional battles their inhabitants hacked to death with knives 
