new york and california legislators went 
back to work monday each facing 1 billion in politically unpopular 
spending cuts 
new yorks democratic gov mario cuomo proposed the cuts to 
avoid a projected 1 billion budget deficit for the fiscal year 
ending march 31 
california gov george deukmejian a republican leaving office 
in january says his cuts would allow the nations largest state to 
finish its fiscal year june 30 with a balanced budget or just a 
small deficit 
cuomo has recommended state worker layoffs mandatory and unpaid 
employee furloughs and cuts in state spending on education and 
health care but he proposed no new taxes and has said that this 
deficit unlike ones in the past would not be wiped out by raiding 
reserve funds and borrowing 
its the third consecutive year of budget deficits in new york 
and next year appears no better state comptroller edward regan has 
predicted a potential 3 billion deficit for the new fiscal year 
cuomo has said that cutting back spending was the only way to 
solve new yorks persistent fiscal problems 
i frankly dont believe there are a whole lot of other 
alternatives cuomo has said there is no painless way out of 
this recession 
legislative leaders had been indicating they might be willing to 
leave cuomos proposals largely intact but as rankandfile 
legislators returned monday there were rumblings that negotiations 
had stalled over the weekend 
lets put it this way were not at impasse said geoffrey 
taylor spokesman for democratic assembly speaker mel miller 
