a key to what caused two northwest airlines 
jets to collide on the ground at detroits airport monday could lie 
in the communications between the control tower and both pilots 
national transportation safety board investigators will analyze 
tapes which record cockpit conversations as well as all 
communications between federal air traffic controllers in the tower 
and planes on the ground and in the air around the airport 
planes are not supposed to move on the ground unless air 
traffic controllers say they can said ntsb spokesman ted 
lopatkiewicz the tower has direct control 
the only discretion a pilot has on the ground at an airport is 
the option of aborting his takeoff once clearance for takeoff is 
given lopatkiewicz said 
he said however it was too early to reach any conclusions 
about the detroit accident investigators will look at all aspects 
of pilot and controller actions aircraft construction airport 
design and other factors that might have contributed to the 
accident 
