through its judicial choices the bush administration is 
waging war on the notion of a fair and representative federal 
judiciary nan aron the groups president said in a statement 
nominees to the federal bench continue the reagan 
administrations tradition of hostility toward individual rights 
and restricting access to the courts aron said 
the alliances report also criticized the senate judiciary 
committee for accelerating the confirmation process therefore 
providing less time for senators to consider the qualifications 
of each nominee and for the general public to participate 
president bush is changing the legal landscape aron said 
it is up to the senate judiciary committee and the public to 
ensure that the legal rights of the disadvantaged are not trampled 
in the process 
