for a district court judgeship in thurmonds home state of south 
carolina despite a lack of experience as a courtroom lawyer and a 
low rating from the american bar association 
the alliances report was issued two days after bush signed into 
law a bill that creates 85 new federal judgeships besides these 
newly created slots there are 41 vacancies on the federal bench 
vacancies that bush will soon have an opportunity to fill 
president bush is following the course of his predecessor in 
choosing appellate judges with dependably conservative records and 
in the next two years he will have the opportunity to tilt the 
balance even more the report said 
bush promoted many district judges appointed by reagan to 
circuit court seats positions where ideology is most apt to 
influence judicial decisionmaking the report said 
fifteen of the 23 nominees bush proposed for federal circuit 
courts were district court judges that reagan had first appointed 
