the baltic rpublics of latvia lithuania and estonia refused to 
participate in drafting the document and have said they will not 
sign it 
if the baltic republics dont accept such a treaty in my 
opinion they will remain in the soviet union on the basis of the 
documents with which they joined the union nishanov told the 
legislature 
he added that under the soviet constitution the baltic 
republics have a right to secede but only if they first hold 
referendums and then follow rules established by the national 
legislature those procedures could entail a waiting period of five 
years repayment for soviet investments and resettlement of 
russianspeaking people now living in the baltics 
latvia lithuania and estonia were occupied by the soviet army 
at the start of world war ii and were annexed in 1945 the kremlin 
has refused to recognize their declarations of independence this 
