the national football league commissioner 
vindicated sports writer lisa olson by imposing 22500 in fines on 
three new england patriots players she accused of sexually taunting 
her in the team locker room 
commissioner paul tagliabue on nov 27 also fined the team 
50000 for being slow to investigate allegations that zeke mowatt 
michael timpson and robert perryman exposed themselves or made lewd 
comments to the boston herald reporter 
mowatt who earlier was fined 2000 by the team was fined 
12500 timpson and perryman were fined 5000 each the fines are 
likely to hurt their reputations more than their bank accounts but 
olson said she accepted the penalties 
my satisfaction with the investigation and subsequent 
sanctions is surpassed only by my wish the disgraceful incident had 
never occurred in the first place she said in a statement 
it was not my choice to have this matter decided in a public 
forum and it is unfortunate that patriot management forced this to 
happen by not dealing with the guilty persons swiftly and 
decisively 
tagliabue agreed saying the team did not adequately 
investigate and resolve a serious incident of misconduct in the 
clubs locker room and appeared to condone the misconduct of the 
patriots players 
the commissioner levied the fines based on a 60page report by 
harvard law professor philip heymann on the sept 17 incident the 
report by heymann as tagliabues special counsel resulted from 
107 interviews with 91 people 
heymann cited discrepancies between the accounts given by olson 
and several players but he said mowatts story was not credible 
and he concluded the reporter suffered sexual taunting by naked 
players 
tagliabue called the players actions completely uncalled for 
and improper mowatts conduct involved both verbal and 
demonstrative actions timpson and perryman encouraged the 
misconduct 
the decision has been rendered now its time to get on with 
playing football patriots owner victor kiam said in a statement 
the penalties are subject to appeal but kiam said the team will 
abide by the decision 
there was no comment immediately afterward from mowatt timpson 
or perryman who is now with the dallas cowboys after being cut by 
new england 
in addition to a 25000 fine for dragging its feet on the 
