the mossy gloom of the graveyard the 
wild beauty of the moor beyond recall the village charlotte bronte 
described as such a lonely spot buried away from the world 
the view from the parsonage parlor where anne emily and 
charlotte wrote their books by candlelight is as somber as ever 
but down the path past the black bull pub where their brother 
branwell sought nightly oblivion is a street for other times 
