<TEXT>
remembrances of the german invasion of the soviet 
union nearly 50 years ago still evoke strong emotions despite the 
end of the cold war 
the invasion came on june 22 1941 beginning a siege that cost 
20 million soviet lives 
and with the reunification of the two germanys this year many 
