caps and more genuine antique icons 
hey oncle sam you want hero medals called out a boy barely 
in his teens opening his coat like a prohibition bootlegger to 
display a lining resplendent with medals ribbons and decorations 
no what about a meelitary vatch he pushed up his sleeve and 
revealed an armload reaching beyond the elbow maybe you give me 
choongum or a marlboro cigarette 
our guide warned against pickpockets money changers who will 
give you prerevolution ukrainian notes and similar bad peoples 
since soviet president mikhail gorbachev lifted the lid on 
communisms pressure cooker all sorts of bad peoples have 
bubbled to the surface in the soviet union crime has risen nearly 
40 per cent in some larger cities where burglaries are up 80 
percent the citizens are forming neighborhood crime patrols 
the police always despised but now ridiculed and rationed to 5 
gallons of gas a day for their patrol cars keep such a low profile 
that highway accidents have increased fourfold 
director vladimir malinin of intourist recently reported that 
because of the crime situation bookings dropped 40 per cent in 
1990 and american visitors were down to 100000 from 180000 the 
year before 
heavy morning fog at odessa on the northern rim of the black sea 
delayed the docking of our ship the cunard liner vistaford 
because we arrived late and the driver is not permitted 
overtime our guide vetoed a photo opportunity at the foot of the 
famous potemkin steps twice as wide at the bottom as the top the 
staircase projects a splendid optical illusion of even greater 
height than its 455 feet 
grigori potemkin catherine the greats favorite general 
ushered in the golden age of tourism on the black sea in 
inaugurating the new harbor at sevastapol in 1797 he floated 
foreign dignitaries down the dnieper on 80 roman galleys painted 
red and gold each with its own orchestra 
since some of the new towns planned for the crimea were still on 
the drawing board potemkin had facades of fake buildings erected 
and transported in thousands of peasants to populate his potemkin 
villages a sort of disneyland on the dnieper 
our guide dismissed an enchanting orthodox cathedral with golden 
onion domes as not important and attempted to hurry us into the 
hardcurrency beryozka shop which sold vodka fur hats amber 
jewelry and other luxury items available only to foreigners 
the way was blocked by a very drunken comrade being rushed along 
by two friends in almost as bad shape he teetered from their grasp 
and fell on his face in the gutter blood gushing from his cuts 
somogan spat out our guide in disgust the word means 
moonshine vodka a popular blackmarket item in the wake of 
gorbachevs temperance campaign 
saturday evidently was marrying day in odessa dozens of wedding 
parties emerged from a government registry office to pose for 
pictures on the lawn and under the porticoes of the handsome opera 
house one of europes finest 
the brides in long white gowns the grooms in formal wear some 
with top hats arrived in horsedrawn carriages and vintage 
limousines gaily decorated with flowers streamers and silver 
bells 
some alighted from taxicabs and the tandem threecar trolleys 
one bride was delivered by an ambulance driven by a friend or 
relative most bridal couples were in their 30s and beyond 
they marry late because there is a long wait for an apartment 
sometimes 10 years a taxi driver told us many will move in 
with relatives 
downtown odessa with its broad boulevards chestnut trees and 
the fading elegance of its hotels museums opera house and older 
apartments built in czarist baroque retains the charm of an older 
europe but that vanishes as one proceeds past the university to 
the grim blocks of tower apartments in communist concrete 
gradually the clock is being turned back in odessa rival 
political parties are beginning to emerge proletariat street has 
changed its name back to french boulevard 
before bidding us farewell the lady from intourist delivered 
one of those stupefying tourguide statistcs that trouble your 
sleep like the rumblings of an underdone blini unsurpassed in 
its curative qualities the mud of odessa has long been recognized 
as the world standard for mud 
east of berlin local color is where you find it 
