<TEXT>
whistling may be on the wane but it has had its moments in 
american musical history 
whistling figured prominently in several movies notably the 
bridge on the river kwai and the high and the mighty and of 
course walt disneys seven dwarfs in snow white whistled while 
they worked 
whistling also helped define disneys oldest and most popular 
character mickey mouse early cartoons depict mickey strolling 
along hands clasped behind his back face tilted to the sky lips 
puckered 
more recently jason serinus of los angeles has provided the 
whistling voice of woodstock snoopys feathered friend on the 
charlie brown specials 
the cheerfully whistled theme song of the 1960s situation comedy 
mayberry rfd still lives on in reruns 
a few songs celebrate the art whistling in the dark for 
instance or whistle a happy tune from the king and i other 
songs include whistled passages the 1970s rock n roll song 
hocus pocus consisted only of instrumental music interspersed 
with yodeling and manic whistling 
movie and cartoon characters have long used whistling as an 
obvious disguise for guilt ineffective talk is whistling in the 
wind nonsensical talk is just whistling dixie a gesture of 
false courage is whistling past the graveyard 
whistling also has its superstitions 
some hold that whistling inside a house is as risky as opening 
an umbrella indoors well into the 20th century whistling aboard 
ship was said to summon up a gale whistling in a theater was 
believed to doom the current production and veteran journalists 
swear its bad luck to whistle in a newsroom 
some cultures have prohibited whistling altogether arab 
countries consider it evil and victorian etiquette books 
pronounced it vulgar at least for women 
some people are annoyed by whistling or find it tiresome no 
more tiresome though than their stock remark did you have 
birdseed for lunch 
</TEXT>
