<TEXT>
success has has not been sweet for was not 
was 
for years they were a funny funky detroit band with singers 
sweet pea atkinson and sir harry bowens songwriters david and don 
was and a handful of listeners their first two albums bombed they 
spent much of the 1980s bouncing around europe 
that made sense to david and don perpetual outsiders pariahs 
with pride they expected mistreatment at the hands of the record 
industry theyd rather crash parties than be invited 
but for the past two years separately and together the wases 
couldnt lose walk the dinosaur and spy in the house of 
love were hit singles their third album what up dog went 
gold don was topped that by producing platinum records for bonne 
raitt and the b52s 
suddenly everybody wanted to know about was not was and when 
they got around to making their next record are you ok they 
felt selfconscious sensitive to the presence of spies in the 
house of was 
i actually feel this is a fine record said david 
interviewed with don was at a manhattan hotel but im glad we 
got rid of it the followup to a hit its like having a genius 
kid and the next kid grows up and all you can see is the new kid in 
the image of the older one i think the next one well lose the 
jitters the pressurell be off or something 
we thought we had a soft image nothing like we really were 
don added we went in the studio and the album took on a life of 
its own it was nothing like we planned 
after are you ok they may have to start crashing parties 
again the album has quickly vanished from the charts they knew 
they were in trouble from the first single a british aampr artist 
and repertoire man urged the wases to take advantage of their 
motown roots and topnotch singers why not cover that old 
temptations hit papa was a rollin stone 
they had performed the song in concert with great success so 
they gave it a shot in the studio sticking closely to the original 
version 
the single flopped 
don put a nice beat under it but otherwise it was 
fruitless david said the singers are too close they can do 
the temptations practically 
we liked the song it was a chance to pay homage to our soul 
