had lived all over the country and was estranged from his mother 
his parents had separated and his younger brother toby author 
tobias wolff who wrote of his own childhood in this boys 
life 
in 1968 geoffrey wolff wrote his first novel bad debts a 
story based on the relationship with his father who died in 1970 
after spending his final years in a sanitarium besides duke of 
deception wolff has since written four novels and the black 
sun a bleak study of poet harry crosby 
the final club takes nathaniel through his years at 
princeton offering judgments on fraternities writers and the 
elitist student body and into a troubled marriage 
the origin of the books title keeps shifting at first its an 
alternative club nathaniel forms with his princeton friends the 
name coming from a card game in which you can be defeated by 
holding the final club 
but the world changes and the title eventually means something 
much deeper that was the final club nathaniel thinks when he 
learns of a death in his family everyone was a member not 
exclusive in the least all comers were goers 
the book ends at the beginning with nathaniel looking ahead to 
the next time he can ponder the final club hes a middleaged 
man who knows his life will never be the same so all he can do is 
what wolff aims for himself behave well to others and try to 
maintain his capacity for wonder 
he has to a degree an obsession about time passing wolff 
said its like that wonderful line burt lancaster delivers in 
atlantic city he looks out over the boardwalk and says when i 
was a boy there was a real ocean its a line that breaks your 
heart 
