the number of working oil and gas rigs in the 
united states remained unchanged this week at 1175 following a 
healthy rebound the week before baker hughes inc reported monday 
the number of rigs had plummeted by 41 in late november 
following heavy rains in oklahoma then rebounded last week by 72 
as weather improved and the endofyear seasonal upturn began a 
year ago this week the number of working rigs was 1062 
decreases in the previous weeks followed a milestone earlier in 
the month when the number of working rigs reached 1144 a figure 
not seen since dec 28 1987 
baker hughes has kept track of the rig count the widely 
watched index of drilling activity since 1940 the count 
represents the number of rigs actively exploring for oil not those 
producing oil 
at the height of the oil boom in december 1981 the count 
reached a peak of 4500 but the rig count plunged to a low of 663 
after oil prices collapsed in the summer of 1986 
oklahoma led the major oil producing states for the week adding 
13 rigs to the count followed by pennsylvania which added six 
michigan which added 2 and north dakota and ohio which each 
added one 
