are here are straight the reason they turn away people is that 
theyre different she was banned from the mall when she sat on a 
bench to rest is that a valid reason to kick someone out she 
asked 
by and large mckinley merchants say the ban has not affected 
business as much as they feared 
ron jefferson who runs the singing river mall in gautier 
miss which attracts as many as 200 teens on a weekend has put in 
an outside entrance to the game rooms to divert traffic he has 
also put in extra security and more phones at the theaters on 
visits to local schools he reminds teens that they are potential 
mall employees as well as patrons 
malls have been havens for teenagers almost from the beginning 
in fact mall owners took pains to attract them with movie theaters 
game rooms record stores the difference today is their sheer 
numbers 
managers are trying innovations to attract teens one offers 
vacant space to a church group which has set up dropin 
counseling another features fashion shows with high school 
students as models 
says one manager when i was a kid i didnt have an american 
express card but these kids do they spend a lot of money here 
